│  }
▼
─────────────────────────────────────
API GATEWAY
─────────────────────────────────────
│
├── Step 1: Authentication
│          Is user logged in?
│          Valid JWT token?
│          No  → 401 Unauthorized ❌
│          Yes → continue ✅
│
├── Step 2: Authorization
│          Is user allowed to order?
│          Account banned? → 403 Forbidden ❌
│          Normal user    → continue ✅
│
├── Step 3: Rate Limiting
│          Too many requests?
│          Spamming orders? → 429 Too Many Requests ❌
│          Normal rate     → continue ✅
│
├── Step 4: Request Validation
│          Correct format?
│          Missing fields? → 400 Bad Request ❌
│          Valid format   → continue ✅
│
├── Step 5: Convert to Lambda Event
│          {
│            "httpMethod": "POST",
│            "path":       "/orders",
│            "headers":    { "Authorization": "Bearer token" },
│            "body":       "{\"restaurant\": \"KFC\"}"
│          }
│
▼
─────────────────────────────────────
LAMBDA
─────────────────────────────────────
│
├── Step 6: Cold Start? (first request)
│          ┌─────────────────────────┐
│          │ Download code package   │
│          │ Start Python runtime    │
│          │ import boto3            │
│          │ import json             │
│          │ s3 = boto3.client('s3') │
│          │ ~2000ms delay           │
│          └─────────────────────────┘
│
│          OR
│
│          Warm Start? (subsequent requests)
│          ┌─────────────────────────┐
│          │ Container already ready │
│          │ ~0ms delay              │
│          └─────────────────────────┘
│
├── Step 7: lambda_handler runs
│
│          def lambda_handler(event, context):
│
│          │
│          ├── Parse request body
│          │   body       = json.loads(event['body'])
│          │   restaurant = body['restaurant']
│          │   item       = body['item']
│          │   quantity   = body['quantity']
│          │
│          ├── Business logic
